ApplicationFees: The application fee for both domestic and international applicants is $70.
AdditionalInformation: Some applicants to California State University, Long Beach are required to submit additional information beyond the standard application. The specific requirements vary depending on the applicant type and intended major.
AdditionalDeadlines: ### Additional Deadlines at California State University, Long Beach
IsMultipleApplicationsAllowed: Application Policy at California State University, Long Beach Restricts Applicants to a Single Program per Term
IsAnalyticalOptional: California State University, Long Beach, has discontinued its Graduation Writing Assessment Requirement Placement Examination (GPE) as of April 2025. Consequently, the associated GWAR courses (301A and Portfolio courses) are no longer mandatory beginning in the summer of 2025. While these courses may still be available as electives, the removal of the compulsory placement exam and required coursework effectively makes the formal "analytical writing" assessment optional for students.
